  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2013-12-12",
    "date": "2014-03-05T21:34:02Z",
    "text": "Bureau of Consumer Financial Protection-Inspector General Reform Act of 2013 or CFPB-IG Act of 2013 - Amends the Inspector General Act of 1978 to repeal the authority of the Chairman of the Board of Governors of the Federal Reserve System (Board) to appoint the Inspector General of the Consumer Financial Protection Bureau (CFPB).\n\n Amends the Dodd-Frank Wall Street Reform and Consumer Protection Act to create an Inspector General for the CFPB.\n\nRequires the President, within 60 days after enactment of this Act, to appoint a CFPB Inspector General."
  },
